short_description:
This is an implementation continuously under development of Dynamic Syntax, a word-by-word incremental semantic grammar, especially suited to dialogue. The implementation contains the following: 
(1) depth-first and breadth-first parsers and generators, based on hand-crafted domain-specific lexicons but cover a broad range of structures, including relatives and tense; 
(2) a prototype incremental dialogue system, DyLan, based on Jindigo (Skantze & Hjalmarsson, 2010), but using the Dynamic Syntax (Kempson et. al. 2001, Cann et. al. 2005) parser/generator; 
(3) a grammar induction module which learns DS incremental grammars from data (Eshghi et. al. 2013).
For more information on DS, and this implementation, please see the files DSImp_TechReport.pdf, and README.txt included here under "files".
